<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1945,2075]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,429]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,267,1945,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[296,548,1945,1971]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="81" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis box="[296,548,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Pluteus glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described originally based on one African collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Horak, E." box="[1263,1410,1945,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81" pagination="87 - 89" refId="ref7607" refString="Horak, E. (1977) Neue zairische Arten aus der Gattung Pluteus Fr. Bulletin du Jardin Botanique National de Belgique 47: 87 - 89. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3667984" type="journal article" year="1977">Horak 1977</bibRefCitation>
). A second collection was added in a subsequent description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Horak, E. &amp; Heinemann, P." box="[990,1309,1979,2005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81" refId="ref7648" refString="Horak, E. &amp; Heinemann, P. (1978) Flore illustree des champignons d'Afrique centrale 6: Pluteus &amp; Volvariella (complements). National Botanical Garden of Belgium, Meise." type="book" year="1978">Horak &amp; Heinemann 1978</bibRefCitation>
). The nrITS sequence from the 
<typeStatus box="[354,454,2014,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<emphasis box="[472,752,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Goossens-Fontana 5274</emphasis>
) is only 95 to 96 % identical with all other sequences in this species complex, including the other African collection studied by us (
<emphasis box="[972,1110,2048,2075]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Thoen 5546</emphasis>
). We could not obtain a 
<emphasis box="[1409,1451,2049,2075]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">tef1</emphasis>
sequence from the 
<typeStatus box="[351,454,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">holotype</typeStatus>
, but based on nrITS data we consider the 
<typeStatus box="[929,1029,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">holotype</typeStatus>
to be the only collection to represent 
<taxonomicName box="[136,319,193,219]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis box="[136,319,193,219]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[326,473,193,219]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">
Morphologically, the 
<typeStatus box="[441,539,227,253]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">holotype</typeStatus>
collection is characterized by the broadly ellipsoid to ellipsoid basidiospores (Qm = 1.33), lageniform pleuro- and cheilocystidia with rounded to truncate apices, and the presence of pale brown intracellular pigment in some cheilocystidia. All of these characters should be checked in future collections to evaluate their reliability for morphological identification. Cheilocystidial pigmentation has been shown to be a variable character in other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[350,434,366,392]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[350,434,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">Pluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="E. F. Malysheva, Minnis &amp; Justo" authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, Minnis &amp; Justo" box="[504,990,366,393]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="eludens">
<emphasis box="[504,619,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">P. eludens</emphasis>
E.F. Malysheva, Minnis &amp; Justo
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Justo, A. &amp; Caballero, A. &amp; Munoz, G. &amp; Minnis, A. M. &amp; Malysheva, E." box="[1005,1206,366,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" pagination="646 - 655" refId="ref7875" refString="Justo, A., Caballero, A., Munoz, G., Minnis, A. M. &amp; Malysheva, E. (2011 c) Taxonomy of Pluteus eugraptus and morphologically similar taxa. Mycologia 103: 646 - 655. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3852 / 10 - 280" type="journal article" year="2011">
Justo 
<emphasis box="[1072,1129,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2011c
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ditmar) P. Kumm." authorityName="P. Kumm." baseAuthorityName="Ditmar" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phlebophorus">
<emphasis box="[1269,1451,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">P. phlebophorus</emphasis>
(Ditmar) P. Kumm.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Justo, A. &amp; Minnis, A. M. &amp; Ghignone, S. &amp; Menolli Jr, N. &amp; Capelari, M. &amp; Rodriguez, O. &amp; Malysheva, E. &amp; Contu, M. &amp; Vizzini, A." box="[367,570,402,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="82" pagination="453 - 479" refId="ref7779" refString="Justo, A., Minnis, A. M., Ghignone, S., Menolli Jr, N., Capelari, M., Rodriguez, O., Malysheva, E., Contu, M. &amp; Vizzini, A. (2011 b) Species recognition in Pluteus and Volvopluteus (Pluteaceae, Agaricales): morphology, geography and phylogeny. Mycological Progress 10: 453 - 479. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 010 - 0716 - z" type="journal article" year="2011">
Justo 
<emphasis box="[433,489,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2011b
</bibRefCitation>
), and, thus, it is not reliable for species rank identification.
</paragraph>
